          • [ - ] CirdomAkul - member since 18-Sep-15

            I was very surprised with Allegri's decisions both before the game and during the game. Juve's best offensive tool is to attack through the wings and they have strikers precisely for that. Instead he opted for De Sciglio in order to be conservative in defense. The result was they had nothing going on in the right wing. If you follow Atletico Madrid this season, you'd know they have problems in wide areas. Cholo knew defending deep is very dangerous against this juve side and his plans perfectly worked thanks to Allegri's decisions. Playing Dybala and using that system looked very bad even before the game because ususally Juve is not good at attacking through the middle and Atletico are very strong in the middle zones. The result of this was the game moved in a direction that there were many individual duels and Atletico are much better than Juve in that respect. For me it was a disastrous game for Allegri.

            Very few people understand the concept of regression to the mean. Ronaldo was no worse tonight than he frequently was for Real Madrid but at Madrid he and the team enjoyed a remarkable run of good results whereas tonight regression kicked in and bad luck happened. All the guff about Ronaldo stepping up when it mattered in the CL simply a reflection of how stats can deceive when there are not enough games to arrive at a genuine average.
